[p 
	"Shining Soul is an Action RPG by Atlus. It is the first 'Shining' game to not be produced by 
	[a class=extlink href=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camelot_Software_Planning rel=nofollow 
		"Camelot Software Planning
	]a
	", and thus is not considered canon in the 'Shining' universe. However, the game serves as an 
	[a class=extlink href=http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InternalHomage rel=nofollow 
		"internal homage
	]a
	" to much of the 'Shining' series. All of the bosses are major villains from a previous 'Shining' game.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The author manipulates randomly-placed monuments to appear, increasing attack power as much as eight-fold during the run. Additionally, hundreds of critical attacks had to be painstakingly manipulated to allow for enemies to die in a single hit. 
	$LF
]p
